HEADWORD: Yoga
<hw>Yo"ga</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.
<ets>y⟦omac⟧ga</ets> union.]</ety> <def>A species of asceticism among
the Hindoos, which consists in a complete abstraction from all worldly
objects, by which the votary expects to obtain union with the universal
spirit, and to acquire superhuman faculties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

